{
  "stem": "10588.12",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And farther down on the other the bank, there were lots of trees and used to come here and play and run and climb trees.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And this is one of those trees.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I tore my, my sailor suit and learned the lesson never to take chances, as my mother said, on things you cannot afford to lose.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "This castle, [? a few-- ?] it was empty.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this castle, on October 15, 1941, in middle of the night, the Nazis broke in by force to our home and yelled on the gunpoint with dogs, rifles, and yelled [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they chased us out.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we didn't have a chance to take too much.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We left only very few belongings.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we had to-- they forced us in a truck.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they brought us here.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And on October 15, 1941, as I said, was the last time I saw Ciechanow.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And now after 55 years, I'm back.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And my heart is breaking, because the city's here.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But a city that was with so many Jewish people, that vibrated with life, children, with tradition, where my family lived for-- on my mother's side for ne-- from almost from the 16th century-- they came from Germany to Poland.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I come here and nothing is left, only memories.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The Holocaust has taught me many lessons.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The most important lesson it has-- that has-- it has told me that we must never be silent and indifferent when people suffer any place in the world.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We have to be in solidarity with the oppressed and never with the oppressor, to stand up for justice, not to be afraid to speak up, and not to wait til it becomes so horrible where we have lost control of our life.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Right in the beginning, we have to speak up and stand up for justice for everyone.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And other lessons that I have learned, after I have lost everything, I have learned not to take anyone or anything for granted.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because people are the only thing that you cannot replace.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You can replace-- you can build other homes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You can have other possessions.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So what I have learned that there are things you cannot buy without money.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Money's important to buy the necessities.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But there are things you cannot buy for money.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And no power on Earth can ever place the irreplaceable loss of the six million, including the people from Ciechanow, where previously lived so many people.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Less than 200 survived.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And most of those survive the USSR, ironically, only because part of them were sent to the-- were not during Nazi Germany here.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Menschlichkeit, which means humanness, because without menschlichkeit, all science, religion, and education fails.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This I have seen in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Because Dr.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Mengele was-- had two-- the Nazi doctor who made the selections who shall go to the gas chambers and who should live to suffer another day, he's responsible for so many deaths and for experiments on twins and other horrible things that he did.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And yet he had two doctor, doctor degrees.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My body belongs to me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To God belongs my soul.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "To my children belongs my inheritance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My love belongs to all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You cannot love Go and hate people.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It's a contradiction.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And when there is no love, there is destruction.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Thank you.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And God bless you all.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And thank you for the wonderful work that you are doing.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
